===Etymology===
From the {{G.}} trademark ''[[Aspirin]]''.  The word is still used as a trademark in some countries, but has entered the language in common usage in the US and the UK.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|aspirins|-}}

#{{uncountable}} An [[analgesic]] [[drug]], ''[[acetylsalicylic acid]]''.
#{{countable}} A [[tablet]] containing this substance.

